11#ifndef MODULES_VIDEO_CODING_INCLUDE_VIDEO_CODING_H_
12#define MODULES_VIDEO_CODING_INCLUDE_VIDEO_CODING_H_
13
14#include "api/video/video_frame.h"
15#include "api/video_codecs/video_codec.h"
16#include "modules/include/module.h"
17#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/source/rtp_video_header.h"
18#include "modules/video_coding/include/video_coding_defines.h"
19
20namespace webrtc {
21
22class Clock;
23class EncodedImageCallback;
24class VideoDecoder;
25class VideoEncoder;
26struct CodecSpecificInfo;
27
28class VideoCodingModule : public Module {
29 public:
30 // DEPRECATED.
31 static VideoCodingModule* Create(Clock* clock);
32
33 /*
34 * Receiver
35 */
36
37 // Register possible receive codecs, can be called multiple times for
38 // different codecs.
39 // The module will automatically switch between registered codecs depending on
40 // the
41 // payload type of incoming frames. The actual decoder will be created when
42 // needed.
43 //
44 // Input:
45 // - payload_type : RTP payload type
46 // - receiveCodec : Settings for the codec to be registered.
47 // - numberOfCores : Number of CPU cores that the decoder is allowed
48 // to use.
49 //
50 // Return value : VCM_OK, on success.
51 // < 0, on error.
52 virtual int32_t RegisterReceiveCodec(uint8_t payload_type,
53 const VideoCodec* receiveCodec,
54 int32_t numberOfCores) = 0;
55
56 // Register an external decoder object.
57 //
58 // Input:
59 // - externalDecoder : Decoder object to be used for decoding frames.
60 // - payloadType : The payload type which this decoder is bound to.
61 virtual void RegisterExternalDecoder(VideoDecoder* externalDecoder,
62 uint8_t payloadType) = 0;
63
64 // Register a receive callback. Will be called whenever there is a new frame
65 // ready
66 // for rendering.
67 //
68 // Input:
69 // - receiveCallback : The callback object to be used by the
70 // module when a
71 // frame is ready for rendering.
72 // De-register with a NULL pointer.
73 //
74 // Return value : VCM_OK, on success.
75 // < 0, on error.
76 virtual int32_t RegisterReceiveCallback(
77 VCMReceiveCallback* receiveCallback) = 0;
78
79 // Register a frame type request callback. This callback will be called when
80 // the
81 // module needs to request specific frame types from the send side.
82 //
83 // Input:
84 // - frameTypeCallback : The callback object to be used by the
85 // module when
86 // requesting a specific type of frame from
87 // the send side.
88 // De-register with a NULL pointer.
89 //
90 // Return value : VCM_OK, on success.
91 // < 0, on error.
92 virtual int32_t RegisterFrameTypeCallback(
93 VCMFrameTypeCallback* frameTypeCallback) = 0;
94
95 // Registers a callback which is called whenever the receive side of the VCM
96 // encounters holes in the packet sequence and needs packets to be
97 // retransmitted.
98 //
99 // Input:
100 // - callback : The callback to be registered in the VCM.
101 //
102 // Return value : VCM_OK, on success.
103 // <0, on error.
104 virtual int32_t RegisterPacketRequestCallback(
105 VCMPacketRequestCallback* callback) = 0;
106
107 // Waits for the next frame in the jitter buffer to become complete
108 // (waits no longer than maxWaitTimeMs), then passes it to the decoder for
109 // decoding.
110 // Should be called as often as possible to get the most out of the decoder.
111 //
112 // Return value : VCM_OK, on success.
113 // < 0, on error.
114 virtual int32_t Decode(uint16_t maxWaitTimeMs = 200) = 0;
115
116 // Insert a parsed packet into the receiver side of the module. Will be placed
117 // in the
118 // jitter buffer waiting for the frame to become complete. Returns as soon as
119 // the packet
120 // has been placed in the jitter buffer.
121 //
122 // Input:
123 // - incomingPayload : Payload of the packet.
124 // - payloadLength : Length of the payload.
125 // - rtp_header : The parsed RTP header.
126 // - video_header : The relevant extensions and payload header.
127 //
128 // Return value : VCM_OK, on success.
129 // < 0, on error.
130 virtual int32_t IncomingPacket(const uint8_t* incomingPayload,
131 size_t payloadLength,
132 const RTPHeader& rtp_header,
133 const RTPVideoHeader& video_header) = 0;
134
135 // Sets the maximum number of sequence numbers that we are allowed to NACK
136 // and the oldest sequence number that we will consider to NACK. If a
137 // sequence number older than |max_packet_age_to_nack| is missing
138 // a key frame will be requested. A key frame will also be requested if the
139 // time of incomplete or non-continuous frames in the jitter buffer is above
140 // |max_incomplete_time_ms|.
141 virtual void SetNackSettings(size_t max_nack_list_size,
142 int max_packet_age_to_nack,
143 int max_incomplete_time_ms) = 0;
144};
145
146} // namespace webrtc
147
148#endif // MODULES_VIDEO_CODING_INCLUDE_VIDEO_CODING_H_
